comment: Galloway (NYK) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Barton's (DEN) driving shot attempt. Barton initiates the contact on the play.
Lauvergne (DEN) briefly engages with Porzingis (NYK) during rebounding.
Lauvergne (DEN) does not intentionally kick the ball on the play.
Galloway (NYK) cleanly strips the ball from Lauvergne (DEN).
After Barton (DEN) secures the rebound, Porzingis (NYK) and Gallinari (DEN) make incidental contact with one another.
Afflalo (NYK) grabs and holds Lauvergne (DEN) affecting his FOM after he sets the screen.
Porzingis (NYK) and Lauvergne (DEN) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball did not touch Lauvergne (DEN) prior to going OOB was confirmed. Denver retained possession.
Lauvergne (DEN) and Anthony (NYK) make incidental contact with one another that does not affect either player's ability to retrieve the rebound.
Gallinari (DEN) sets the screen on Afflalo (NYK) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Gallinari (DEN) splits his feet on the perimeter.
LATR shows that Afflalo (DEN) makes contact with Gallinari's (DEN) arm that affects his jump shot attempt.
LHH shows that Porzingis (NYK) and Lauvergne (DEN) make incidental contact with one another while reaching for the loose ball.
Calderon (NYK) commits a take foul on Barton (DEN).
Anthony (NYK) moves his pivot foot. The official is looking for any illegal contact and does not pick up the pivot foot.
Gallinari (DEN) maintains legal guarding position as he contests Anthony's (NYK) layup attempt. Anthony initiates any contact on the play.
Calderon (NYK) commits a take foul on Barton (DEN).
